RayTracerR Data Saving Test

Foreword

This notebook is used for developing the function for saving the data in the appropriate format for Jans Parallel Tempered MCMC. Therefore, it mostly goes over the same procedure that is defined in raytraceR.R, but saves data after running the simulation.

Check the ray results if debugging was switched on

read.rays <- function(file = "rays.dat",nrays=1,timeP= NA)
{
  ind.delta <- 2*seq(nrays)-1
  df <- tibble()
  for (i in seq(nrays))
  {
    delta <- c(0,scan(file,skip = ind.delta[i]-1,nlines = 1))
    depth <- c(0,scan(file,skip = ind.delta[i],nlines = 1))
    ray <- i
    df <- bind_rows(df,tibble(delta=delta,depth=depth,ray=ray,ray.label = round(timeP[i],digits=4)  ))
  }
  df <- df %>% group_by(ray) %>% mutate(depth.cum = cumsum(depth), delta.cum = cumsum(delta) )
  return(df)
}
rays.df <- read.rays(nrays=NSrc,timeP = timeP$timeP)

Plot the sampling from the voro_sample file

We need to follow the notation given in prmjh_temper.f90 and read in the numbers accordingly :

sample(ikeep,:) = (/ objm(ic)%logL, objm(ic)%logPr, objm(ic)%tcmp, REAL(objm(ic)%k,RP), & ! 4 parameters tmpvoro,objm(ic)%sdparRT,objm(ic)%arpar,objm(ic)%arparRT, & REAL(iaccept,RP)/REAL(iaccept+ireject,RP),REAL(objm(ic)%iaccept_bd,RP),& REAL(objm(ic)%ireject_bd,RP),REAL(objm(ic)%iaccept_bds,RP),REAL(ic,RP),REAL(rank,RP) /)

Here we setup the names of the columns, as well as read the file with the sample table:

col.names <- c('LogL','LogPrior','tcmp','k')
k <- NLayers+1 # by convention of Jan's RJMCMC
NParamPerLayer <- 2
NVoro <- NLayersMax*NParamPerLayer
col.names.voro <- rep(NA,NVoro)
# Make Voro Column names - this will be my velocity profiles
vel.names <- paste0(('V'),seq(NVoro/2))
depth.names <- paste0(('Z'),seq(NVoro/2))
col.names.voro[seq(1,NVoro-1,by=2)] <- depth.names
col.names.voro[seq(2,NVoro,by=2)] <- vel.names
after.voro.names <- c('SdRT','ArPar','ArParRT','acc_ratio','iacc_bd','irej_bd','iacc_bds','ic','rank')
all.names <- c(col.names,col.names.voro,after.voro.names)
var.to.keep <- c(col.names.voro,'SdRT')
true.model = tibble(variable =c(col.names.voro[order(col.names.voro)],"SdRT"),value = c(v,c(0,d),SdRT))
filename <- '~/RayTracerFortran/RayTracer/test_1/test_1_voro_sample.txt'
chain.df <- read.table(filename) %>% tbl_df() %>% mutate(iter = row_number())
colnames(chain.df)[1:length(all.names)] <- all.names

Marginal distributions

In order to look at the distributions for each parameter, we need to melt the table:

#chain.df <- chain.df %>% filter(Z2>0)
chain.melted <- melt(chain.df,id.vars = 'iter') %>% filter(variable %in% var.to.keep) %>% tbl_df() %>% mutate(value = as.numeric(value))
p <- ggplot(data = chain.melted,aes(x=value,group = variable)) + geom_histogram(bins=100) + facet_wrap(~variable,scales = 'free',ncol = 4) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept=value),data = true.model,col = 'salmon',size=1.2)
p.traces <- ggplot(data = chain.melted,aes(x=iter,group = variable,y=value)) + geom_line() + facet_wrap(~variable,scales = 'free',ncol = 1)
print(p)

Velocity profiles from the chains:

# Profile drawing function:
drawProfiles <- function(x)
{
d=as.numeric(x[(NLayers+2) : (2*(NLayers+1))])
v=as.numeric(x[1:(NLayers+1)])
f <- approxfun(d,v,method = "constant")
dnew <- seq(1,8000,length.out = 200)
vnew <- f(dnew)
vnew[is.na(vnew)] = v[length(v)]
dd <- d[-1]
for (i in seq(length(dd)) )
{
  ptsX=seq(from=min(v[i],v[i+1]),to = max(v[i],v[i+1]),by=40)
  ptsY=rep(dd[i],length(ptsX))
  dnew=c(dnew,ptsY)
  vnew=c(vnew,ptsX)
}
prof <-tbl_df(data.frame(d=dnew,v=vnew))
return(prof)
}
thin=2
burnin =1000
samples <- chain.df %>% select(c(vel.names,depth.names))
samples.thinned <- as.matrix(samples[seq(burnin,nrow(samples),by=thin),1:ncol(samples)])
profs <-do.call("rbind",pblapply(seq(nrow(samples.thinned)), function(i) {df <- drawProfiles(samples.thinned[i,]);df$id=i;return(tbl_df(df))},cl=4)) %>% tbl_df()
